RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Everett, WA operates under a mayor-council form of government with an elected mayor and seven city council members. The Mayor, Cassie Franklin, was re-elected in November 2025 for a third term. The City Council consists of two at-large members and five district representatives. As of November 10, 2025, the 2025 election results are still being certified (certification on November 25, 2025). Therefore, the listed council members are the currently serving incumbents. Paula Rhyne, Don Schwab, and Ben Zarlingo were re-elected in the 2025 elections. Mary Fosse and Liz Vogeli were incumbents not seeking re-election in 2025, and their successors' election results are pending final certification.
